      <TextArea editable="false" layoutX="63.0" layoutY="100.0" prefHeight="323.0" prefWidth="846.0" text="First plug in the Agua:Bit and go to the Update screen. If this is your first time, make sure you are connected to the internet and press the &quot;Update&quot; button. The required file for the Agua:Bit will be downloaded to your documents folder. After the download is done press the &quot;Update&quot; button again and the file will be uploaded to the Agua:Bit. The Agua:Bit can now be used.&#10;&#10;Head over to the Connect tab and select the sensors that will be used in the measurement. Make sure to select the correct slots and the corresponding options. After that press the &quot;Send to Agua:Bit&quot; button and wait till the confirmation message appears.&#10;&#10;To make a measurement, make sure the sensors are firmly connected to the slot selected in the Connect tab. Go to the Measure tab and click &quot;Measure&quot;. The measured values should now appear on the screen." wrapText="true" AnchorPane.bottomAnchor="200.0" AnchorPane.leftAnchor="55.0" AnchorPane.rightAnchor="55.0" />
